Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.17,0:00:14.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人终难免一死？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Must we die?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.24,0:00:19.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙中有没有长生不死的生物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Are there beings in the cosmos who live forever...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.82,0:00:26.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可以永远逍遥地游在时间之河上？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}afloat on an endless journey down the river of time?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.00,0:01:57.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\fe134}{\fsp0}{\fad(500,500)}{\pos(190,278)}{\fn方正准圆简体}{\bord0}{\fs20}{\c&H24EFFF&}宇宙大探索\N{\fs17}{\c&HFFFFFF&} 第十一集
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.29,0:02:10.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的先祖依靠的是月亮与星星为时间分段时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our ancestors marked the passage of time by the Moon and stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.39,0:02:43.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可在大约5000年前 在这里生活过的人们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it was the people who once lived here, around 5,000 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.29,0:02:45.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们开始把时间分为\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who first starting chopping up time
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.13,0:02:48.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}小时和分钟这样更小的部分\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into smaller bite-sized portions of hours and minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.03,0:02:51.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当时这个地方叫做乌鲁克\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They call this place Uruk.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.46,0:02:54.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们现在称之为伊拉克\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We call it Iraq.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.50,0:02:56.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这里是位于底格里斯河与幼发拉底河之间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a part of Mesopotamia,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.24,0:02:59.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}美索不达米亚平原的一部分\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the land between the Tigris and the Euphrates rivers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.31,0:03:05.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人们在这里创建了城市\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The city was invented here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.35,0:03:07.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在与时间无尽的战斗中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And one of humanity's greatest victories was won
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.91,0:03:10.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}取得了人类历史上一个伟大的成就\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the ceaseless battle against time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.35,0:03:13.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人类在这里学会了如何书写\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was here that we learned how to write.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.39,0:03:15.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}死亡再也不能让人默默无闻\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Death could no longer silence us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.69,0:03:17.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}书写给予了人类力量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And writing gave us the power
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.72,0:03:19.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让我们可以逾越千年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to reach across the millennia
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.83,0:03:22.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与古人交流精神\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and speak inside the heads of the living.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.56,0:03:24.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}历史上没有人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No one has ever spoken
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.83,0:03:26.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}能穿越如此之长的时间之河\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}across a longer stretch of time's river
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.00,0:03:28.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}除了阿卡德帝国的公主\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than this Akkadian princess,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.70,0:03:31.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她是历史上第一位君王的女儿\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}daughter of the first emperor in history,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.17,0:03:34.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也被称为月亮公主――恩西杜安娜\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and priestess of the Moon-- Enheduanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.41,0:03:36.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她不仅仅会写诗歌\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For not only did she write poetry,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.88,0:03:38.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恩西杜安娜还做了其它一些\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but Enheduanna did something
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.04,0:03:40.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}前人没有做过的事情\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}no one before her had ever done--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.68,0:03:43.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她在作品上署上自己的名字\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}she signed her name to her work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.22,0:03:45.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可以说 她是历史上第一个\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}She's the first person for whom we can say
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.42,0:03:47.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们知道确切身份\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we know who she was,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.39,0:03:49.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也知道她的梦想世界的人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and what she dreamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.29,0:03:53.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她一直梦想着能走进神奇之门\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}She dreamt of stepping through the Gate of Wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.23,0:03:55.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是恩西杜安娜所想\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here's a thought Enheduanna sent
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.93,0:03:58.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它穿越了4000年的时光来到我们身边\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}across more than 4,000 years to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.93,0:04:01.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}下面就是她的作品\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's from her work entitled
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.47,0:04:03.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}名为《小女雄心》\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Lady of the Largest Heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.11,0:04:10.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}英娜娜 天上的金星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Innana, the planet Venus,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.78,0:04:14.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}爱的女神\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}goddess of love, will have a great destiny
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.15,0:04:17.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你是宇宙伟大的主宰\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}throughout the entire universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.22,0:04:20.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙的主宰\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}...throughout the entire universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.12,0:04:22.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}乌鲁克也是史诗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And Uruk is also the place where the epic tale
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.96,0:04:25.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}《英雄的旅程》首次创作的地方\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of "The Hero's Journey" was first written down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.49,0:04:28.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}远在蝙蝠侠 天行者卢克\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Before Batman, Luke Skywalker,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.30,0:04:30.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}奥德赛――这些英雄诞生之前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Odysseus-- before them all--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.40,0:04:33.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}传说有一个人叫吉尔伽美什\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there was a man named Gilgamesh
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.73,0:04:37.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他为了能征服时间而远离了家乡\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who left home on a quest to vanquish time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.50,0:04:40.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}吉尔伽美什寻觅着长生不死的方法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gilgamesh was searching for immortality.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.57,0:04:42.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他走遍四方\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He looked everywhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.01,0:04:44.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}获得了无上的智慧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}gained complete wisdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.84,0:04:47.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}发现了隐藏的秘密\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}uncovered what was hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.61,0:04:51.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他带着一堆大洪水时代之前的传奇回到了家乡\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He brought back a tale of times before the Great Flood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.69,0:04:57.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他建造了后世的君王没有能与他媲美的乌鲁克城池\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He built the Wall of Uruk, which no future king will ever match.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.79,0:05:00.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}吉尔伽美什的故事\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Read the story of that man Gilgamesh,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.33,0:05:02.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}描述了一个在乌鲁克诞生的英雄\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a hero born of Uruk,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.83,0:05:05.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他经历了千辛万苦\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who went through all kinds of sufferings.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.47,0:05:06.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}远渡重洋\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Who crossed the ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.93,0:05:09.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}去到太阳升起的地方\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the broad seas, as far as the sunrise;
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.87,0:05:11.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}世界的尽头\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who inspected the edges of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.84,0:05:14.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只为了寻觅永生的奥秘\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}searching for eternal life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.37,0:05:15.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在旅途中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On his travels,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.84,0:05:19.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}吉尔伽美什遇到了一位名为乌特纳比西丁的智者\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gilgamesh encountered a wise man named Utnapishtim,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.05,0:05:22.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}智者告诉了他大洪水曾把世界毁灭\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who told him the story of a flood that destroyed the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.72,0:05:25.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一位神明指示乌特纳比西丁\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and how one of the gods instructed Utnapishtim
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.82,0:05:30.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}造出方舟 拯救他的家人与动物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to build an ark to rescue his family and the animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.42,0:06:06.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是世界上最早的关于大洪水的传说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The earliest surviving account of the flood legend
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.49,0:06:08.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它产生于美索不达米亚\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was written down in Mesopotamia,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.53,0:06:11.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}直到1000年后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a thousand years before it was retold
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.10,0:06:13.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}《圣经・旧约》中才出现诺亚方舟的故事\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as the story of Noah in the Old Testament.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.83,0:06:15.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可以这么说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, you could say Gilgamesh
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.90,0:06:18.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}吉尔伽美什圆满地完成了他对永生的追求\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}fulfilled his quest for immortality.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.10,0:06:21.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是今天的《吉尔伽美什史诗》\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We still read the Epic of Gilgamesh,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.11,0:06:24.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人们每读一次 他就再生一次\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and with every reader, he lives again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.08,0:06:27.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}自从人类第一部英雄史诗诞生以来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And all those heroes and superheroes who have come since
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.51,0:06:31.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}历史上还涌现出无数的英雄与超级英雄\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}follow in the footsteps of the first hero's journey--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.45,0:06:34.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这可被视为某种形式的永生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}another kind of immortality;
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.42,0:06:37.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}随人类文明而流传的故事\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a story sent from one civilization to another
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.52,0:06:39.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}跨越千年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}across thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.86,0:06:43.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但生命本身也有自己的故事\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But life itself sends its own stories
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.10,0:06:45.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}流传了好几百万年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}across billions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.87,0:06:51.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它就是我们每个人体内都携带的信息\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a message that every one of us carries inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.97,0:06:54.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}烙印在我们的细胞之中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}inscribed in all the cells of our bodies,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.74,0:06:58.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它用地球上的生命都知晓的语言书写\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a language that all life on Earth can read.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.21,0:07:01.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}基因的密码表上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The genetic code is written in an alphabet
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.55,0:07:03.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只有4个字母\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}consisting of only four letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.15,0:07:07.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个字母代表着由原子组成的一个分子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each letter is a molecule made of atoms;
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.05,0:07:09.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个单词由3个字母组成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}each word is three letters long.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.62,0:07:13.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个生命都是了不起的杰作\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every living thing is a masterpiece,
