Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.07,0:09:01.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但直到70年后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But 70 years would pass
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.07,0:09:03.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人们才懂得如何解读\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before anyone could read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.67,0:09:08.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1976年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1976,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.68,0:09:13.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}美国航天局将两艘维京号探测器送上了火星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NASA landed two Viking spacecraft on Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.25,0:09:14.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}卡尔・萨根把我们引向那里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Carl Sagan took us there
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.85,0:09:17.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在人类探索宇宙的早期\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on our original journey through the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.78,0:09:19.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们发现火星的大气\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We found that the Martian air
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.55,0:09:21.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比地球稀薄\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was less than one percent as dense as ours,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.79,0:09:24.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大部分由二氧化碳组成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and made mostly of carbon dioxide.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.22,0:09:27.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有小部分的氮\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There were smaller amounts of nitrogen,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.09,0:09:30.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}氩 水蒸气与氧气\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}argon, water vapor and oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.86,0:09:32.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几年后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A few years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.40,0:09:34.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当科学家们想要分析\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when scientists thought to analyze the gasses
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.94,0:09:36.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}纳卡拉陨石中含有的气体\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}trapped inside the Nakhla meteorite,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.94,0:09:38.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与及其它的物质成分时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and other members of its class,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.97,0:09:41.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们发现了惊人的相似性\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they found a striking similarity--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.21,0:09:43.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大部分的陨石\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the vast majority of meteorites
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.28,0:09:45.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是小行星的碎片\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are fragments of asteroids.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.55,0:09:48.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但落在地球上的这块纳卡拉陨石\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the kind that hit Nakhla, on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.25,0:09:51.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只有可能来自一个地方……\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could only have come from one place...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.66,0:10:04.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那就是火星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.02,0:10:11.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}欢迎来到火星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Welcome to Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.09,0:10:19.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}十亿年前 这里的一座火山爆发了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Over a billion years ago, a volcano erupted here
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.36,0:10:22.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}岩浆冷却后形成了岩石\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and its lava cooled into solid rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.16,0:10:24.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几百万年后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hundreds of millions of years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.43,0:10:27.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这块地方被洪水所淹没\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this area was flooded with water.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.47,0:10:29.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}洪水过后很多年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And long after that flood,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.14,0:10:31.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一块有直布罗佗岩石那么大的小行星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an asteroid the size of the Rock of Gibraltar
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.50,0:10:34.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}撞击了火星表面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}crashed into the Martian surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.17,0:10:36.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}炸出一个大坑\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}blasting out a huge crater.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.51,0:10:43.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大部分的碎片被弹到太空\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Much of the debris was ejected back out into space,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.12,0:10:45.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}碎片一开始绕着太阳旋转\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where it orbited the Sun until a gravitational tug
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.95,0:10:49.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}直到来自火星的引力把其中一个石块\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from its home planet, Mars, diverted one of the boulders
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.12,0:10:51.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}转向与地球碰撞的轨道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into a collision course with Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.62,0:10:55.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它最终抵达了纳卡拉村\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its arrival shook up the little village of Nakhla.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.80,0:10:58.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}像纳卡拉这样类型的陨石\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Meteorites of the type that hit Nakhla
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.46,0:11:02.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是星际间天然的运输系统\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are the vehicles of a natural interplanetary transit system
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.80,0:11:05.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它在行星之间输送石块\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that sends rocks between the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.24,0:11:09.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}像这样的陨石可以把微小的"货物"安全运抵目的地\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Such a meteorite can safely shelter microscopic cargo--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.68,0:11:11.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那就是生命的种子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the seeds of life--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.98,0:11:14.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它就是星际方舟\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an interplanetary ark.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.65,0:11:18.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大部分的岩石是多孔的 有细小的角落和缝隙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most rocks are porous, full of tiny nooks and crannies,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.32,0:11:20.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很适合生命用来偷渡\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where life can stow away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.16,0:11:25.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们已经发现好几种微生物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We know that some microbes can survive
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.03,0:11:29.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}能在恶劣的太空环境下生存\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the hostile environment of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.16,0:11:31.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比如说 像这些小伙伴们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Take these guys, for instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.93,0:11:35.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些微生物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These microbes spent a year and a half riding
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.17,0:11:37.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在国际空间站外放置了一年半\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the outside of the International Space Station,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.74,0:11:41.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们暴露在极端的温度与真空下\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}exposed to the extreme temperatures, vacuum,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.04,0:11:43.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有宇宙幅射\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and radiation of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.18,0:11:46.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但它们中的一部分在被带回到地球之后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And some of them were still alive and kicking
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.38,0:11:49.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}仍然生龙活虎\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when they were brought back to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.05,0:11:51.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些生物还有更令人惊异的一面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even more astonishing are these creatures,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.92,0:11:56.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们能从800万年的假死状态中苏醒\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}awakened from a deathlike sleep of eight million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.69,0:11:58.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们曾被冰封在南极\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They were frozen in the Antarctic ice
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.03,0:12:02.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在人类出现前好几百万年就已存在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}millions of years before our species even existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.96,0:12:04.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而且它们依然活着\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And they're still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.30,0:12:09.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果生命能经受住恶劣的太空环境\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If life can withstand the hardships of space
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.30,0:12:11.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并且千年不死的话\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and endure for millennia,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.44,0:12:14.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那它们就能乘坐着星际快车\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then it could ride the natural interplanetary transit system
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.64,0:12:16.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从一个世界到另一个世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from world to world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.24,0:12:19.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很有可能 我们的微生物先祖们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a good bet that our microbial ancestors
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.05,0:12:21.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是这样从太空降临\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}spent some time in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.15,0:12:22.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为什么我们会如此认为？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why do we think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.78,0:12:26.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球有45亿年的历史\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth is four-and-a-half- billion-years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.12,0:12:30.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在它的诞生初期有一半的时间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For the first half of its lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.99,0:12:32.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都在被巨型小行星轰炸着\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}large asteroids were bombarding the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.93,0:12:36.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}劫难每隔几百万年就来一次\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every few million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.06,0:12:39.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最猛烈的冲击可以让海洋蒸发\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The most violent impacts vaporized the oceans
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.93,0:12:42.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让地表的岩石融化\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and even melted the surface rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.90,0:12:44.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每一次如此巨大的冲击\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each such collision would have
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.97,0:12:46.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都能让星球上的生命全灭\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}completely sterilized the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.64,0:12:49.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并持续好几千年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.21,0:12:53.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但我们从化石中得知\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But we know from fossils in the rocks
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.25,0:12:55.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}细菌早已在地球上生存\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that bacteria were evolving on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.58,0:12:57.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从那段地球形成的早期就已开始\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}during this formative period.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.69,0:13:05.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那生命又是如何逃过这些劫难的呢？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So how could life have survived such a lethal series of blows?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.86,0:13:07.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}任何一次巨大的小行星冲击地球时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Whenever one of those big asteroids
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.43,0:13:10.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}爆炸都会形成大坑\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hit the Earth, the explosion would blast out a crater,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.76,0:13:13.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将几百万块巨石弹入太空\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}launching millions of boulders into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.87,0:13:17.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}许多石头当中有细菌存在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Many of those rocks carried living bacteria inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.80,0:13:20.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有些小生物就能像这样生存在太空中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some of the bugs would have survived in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.14,0:13:23.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而它们留在地球上的同类早已被烤焦了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}while all those left behind on Earth would have been fried.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.41,0:13:26.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}撞击过后几千年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A few thousand years after each impact,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.75,0:13:28.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球又冷却下来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Earth would have cooled down enough
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.92,0:13:31.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}水凝聚为海洋\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for water to condense into oceans.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.42,0:13:35.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球又变得适宜居住了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The planet would again be habitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.22,0:13:38.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与此同时 在太空中的大部分石头\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Meanwhile, most of the rocks launched into space
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.46,0:13:42.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}正在绕着太阳转\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would have been orbiting the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.33,0:13:45.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们当中的一部分将会重新与地球相遇\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some of them would encounter the Earth again,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.46,0:13:48.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}像陨石一样进入地球大气\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}reenter the atmosphere as meteorites,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.40,0:13:50.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将它们携带的珍贵生命\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and deliver their precious cargo of life
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.90,0:13:53.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}重新播洒到这个行星上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to re-seed the planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.11,0:13:57.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如同诺亚方舟\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like Noah's ark.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.18,0:13:59.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果生命不能\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What this means is that life doesn't have
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.41,0:14:03.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}像这样从绝世天劫中重新开始的话\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to start over again from scratch after each catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.98,0:14:06.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它还能从其它地方再来一次\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It can pick up where it left off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.39,0:14:09.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当时太阳系还很年轻\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the solar system was young,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.59,0:14:11.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}金星可能更像地球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Venus was probably more like Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.79,0:14:14.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有海洋 甚至有生命\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with oceans and maybe even life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.96,0:14:18.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}金星 地球 火星都由于陨石冲击\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Venus, Earth, and Mars were all exchanging rocks
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.26,0:14:20.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而在互相传送石头\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with each other, due to asteroid impacts.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.20,0:14:23.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球上的生命有没有\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Does life on Earth carry any traces
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.37,0:14:25.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}携带着这些遥远的星际迷航的线索？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of interplanetary voyages made in the distant past?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.01,0:14:29.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为什么有些微生物能\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why is it that some microbes can survive
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.38,0:14:32.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在强烈的辐射与真空的太空中活着？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the intense radiation and vacuum of space?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.78,0:14:36.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这样的环境根本就不在地球上存在过\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These conditions don't naturally exist on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.15,0:14:38.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也许这些小生物在告诉我们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maybe those bugs are telling us
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.05,0:14:42.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们的先祖从几百万年前开始\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that their ancestors survived those same conditions in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.29,0:14:44.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就已经是这样在太空中活着\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a few billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.63,0:14:48.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}既然我们知道了微生物能通过石头\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we know that microbes can stow away in rocks
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.13,0:14:50.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在行星之间飞渡\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and survive the voyage from planet to planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.86,0:14:53.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那有没有可能从恒星到恒星？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what about trip from star to star--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.37,0:14:55.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}实现更广阔的星系旅行？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an interstellar odyssey?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.82,0:15:05.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}蒲公英\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The dandelion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.92,0:15:08.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有3000万年的历史\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Around 30 million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.39,0:15:11.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它拥有把自身的生命信息传递出去的不同方式\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it evolved another way to send its own message of life
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.93,0:15:14.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那就是通过时空\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}through space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.00,0:15:25.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每一个种子都是一个小伞兵\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each seedling is a little paratrooper,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.07,0:15:26.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它漂浮在空气中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}floating on the wind,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.74,0:15:30.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}上下浮沉 寻找一个安全之所\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}risking everything for a safe place to land.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.78,0:15:35.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}上升气流能把它们带到高空\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Updrafts can carry them higher into the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.15,0:15:36.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}蒲公英能穿越数十\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A dandelion can travel dozens,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.58,0:15:38.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}或者是数百公里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}possibly hundreds of kilometers,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.65,0:15:43.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}甚至能跨过高山\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even crossing over mountain ranges.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.19,0:15:47.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}进化将它塑造成为精妙的飞行器\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Evolution has shaped it into an exquisite flying machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.00,0:15:50.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的种子就是另一种方舟\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The seed is another kind or ark,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.70,0:15:52.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}确保物种得以存活\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ensuring the survival of its species
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.60,0:15:56.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}乘风飘往安全之地\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by riding the currents of the atmosphere to safe harbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.10,0:15:59.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个种子里的DNA都藏着一个故事\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each seed in its DNA carries a story,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.47,0:16:02.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那就是下一代蒲公英的特征与命运\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the character and destiny of the next dandelion--
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.68,0:16:06.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}生命通过复制自身而传播出去\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}life propagates by retelling its story.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.38,0:16:11.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那生命有没有可能\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is it possible that life could survive the journey
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.79,0:16:13.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在恒星到恒星的旅行中存活下来？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from star to star?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.79,0:16:16.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒星之间的距离要比\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The stars are about a million times farther apart
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.66,0:16:19.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}行星之间的距离多出一百万倍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from each other than are the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.23,0:16:23.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}距离是如此的遥远 以至于要好几百万年后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Space is so vast that it would take billions of years
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.16,0:16:25.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球的石头才会抵达那里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for a rock ejected from the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.03,0:16:29.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然后与围绕另一颗恒星运转的行星相遇\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to collide with a planet circling another star.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.80,0:16:32.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有微生物能够\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Any stowaway microbes would never survive
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.81,0:16:35.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在如此长时间的宇宙幅射下存活\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the cosmic radiation for that long.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.14,0:16:37.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但有一个可行的方案\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there's a plausible scenario
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.04,0:16:40.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可以实现生命从太阳系向另一星系的传播\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for how life could spread from one solar system to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.59,0:16:48.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}银河系的恒星受引力的驱动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The stars of the Milky Way are drawn by gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.99,0:16:53.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们在自己的巨大轨道中绕着银河中心运行\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in their own enormous orbits around its center.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.23,0:16:55.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比如我们的太阳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our Sun, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.16,0:16:59.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每隔2亿2千5百万年就完成一次轨道运行\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}takes some 225 million years to complete a single orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.87,0:17:03.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在每次绕银河系公转中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}During each revolution around the galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.10,0:17:06.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳系会穿越2到3个\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our solar system will pass through two or three
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.11,0:17:08.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}巨大的星际云\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}gigantic interstellar clouds,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.54,0:17:12.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个星际云都有好几光年宽\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}each of them many light years across.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.75,0:17:19.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}银河系是一个巨大的星球工厂\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Galaxies are world-making machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.02,0:17:23.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的银河中有超过100个这样的大型星云\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our Milky Way has more than 100 of these vast clouds,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.69,0:17:26.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}气体和尘埃在那里聚集\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a place where gas and dust condense
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.29,0:17:28.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}形成新的恒星与行星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to form new stars and planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.30,0:17:34.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在银河的旅途中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In its travels through the Milky Way,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.64,0:17:37.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳不仅由其行星相伴\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our Sun is accompanied not only by its planets,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.64,0:17:41.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而且还有数以万亿的遥远的彗星跟随\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but also by a trillion distant comets.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.11,0:17:46.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当太阳系穿过星际云时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When our solar system passes through an interstellar cloud,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.45,0:17:48.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}巨大星云的引力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the gravity of the massive cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.75,0:17:52.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牵动了最外层的彗星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}stirs up the outermost comets.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.45,0:17:55.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有些彗星被扔出到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some comets will be hurled out
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.26,0:17:57.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒星间的空间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into the space between the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.79,0:18:02.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有些则被拉进了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Others will plunge inward...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.60,0:18:07.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}直奔太阳的路线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}falling towards the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.08,0:18:26.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们中的一部分可能会与行星相撞\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And some of them may collide with the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.86,0:18:31.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}彗星以高速碰撞了多岩石的行星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The high-speed impact of a comet with a rocky planet
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.43,0:18:34.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将大量的石头抛入太空\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will launch boulders like rockets into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.86,0:18:37.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果这个星球上正好有生命存在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If that planet should happen to be inhabited,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.77,0:18:40.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那么这许多的石头中就会有乘客\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}many of those rocks will carry passengers--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.47,0:18:42.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}活的微生物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}living microbes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.80,0:18:44.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几千年后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}After thousands of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.77,0:18:47.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球石头的碎块\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}fragments of the rocks ejected from Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.11,0:18:51.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}会像陨石一样落在新生的行星上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can fall as meteors into the atmospheres of newborn planets
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.55,0:18:53.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就在那星际云里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the interstellar cloud.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.72,0:19:02.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那些偷渡的微生物们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If the stowaway microbes
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.32,0:19:05.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果正好遇到了液态水\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}should happen to come in contact with liquid water,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.19,0:19:08.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们就会开始复苏并不断复制\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they can revive and reproduce.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.80,0:19:11.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}生命也许就是这样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This may be how life comes barreling
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.47,0:19:13.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}进入另一个荒芜的天地\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into the barren places.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.83,0:19:16.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳也是由星云聚集而成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The sun emerges from the cloud,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.37,0:19:17.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它把生命的种子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}having scattered the seeds of life
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.01,0:19:21.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}散播在其它恒星的新生世界中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}among the newborn worlds of other stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.64,0:19:24.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些新世界现在被生命所触及\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those new worlds, now touched by life,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.71,0:19:26.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然后离开它们诞生的星云\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will then leave their birth cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.31,0:19:28.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从此天各一方\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and go their separate ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.52,0:19:30.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最终 这些恒星又会把它们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Eventually, their stars will carry them
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.99,0:19:32.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}带到其它的星际云那里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}through other interstellar clouds,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.42,0:19:36.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也许它们又将散播生命到更多的新世界中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where they may seed still more new worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.26,0:19:41.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想象一下 如果这样的过程在不同的星球之间重复\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Imagine this process repeated from world to world,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.73,0:19:44.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每一次都把生命带给另一个世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}each one bringing life to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.91,0:19:54.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}生命就以这样缓慢的链式反应传播开来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Life would then propagate, like a slow chain reaction,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.91,0:19:57.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}布满整个银河\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}through the entire galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.92,0:20:05.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}生命也许就是如此降临地球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This could be how life came to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.95,0:20:07.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可我们还不能确定\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We do not know for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.96,0:20:11.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}外面是否有像我们一样的生物？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Are there any beings out there like us?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.63,0:20:13.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们是否也在问同样的问题？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Do they ask the same questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.59,0:20:15.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们也会害怕吗？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Do they share our fears?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.60,0:20:18.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们是否也有英雄与传奇？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Do they have heroes and adventures?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.60,0:20:27.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果他们存在 又在哪里？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If they do exist, where are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.48,0:20:29.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们又如何显示他们的存在？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How might they make their presence known?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.09,0:20:49.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人类是如何第一次宣布自己在银河系的存在？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How did we first announce our presence to the galaxy?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.46,0:20:55.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1946年 二战结束后的第二年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was 1946, the year after the Second World War ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.74,0:20:59.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}再生动的想象力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The vivid imaginations
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.77,0:21:01.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就算是韦尔斯的小说和巴克?罗杰斯的探险\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of HG Wells and Buck Rogers
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.61,0:21:03.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们的疯狂也比不上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}never cooked up a more fantastic experience
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.51,0:21:06.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们军队的工程师\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than the Army engineers
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.11,0:21:08.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在新泽西州贝尔马实验室里干的事\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at their laboratory in Belmar, New Jersey.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.32,0:21:10.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它为人类开启了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It opens up unlimited possibilities
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.32,0:21:12.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}星际探险的无限可能性\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for interstellar experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.15,0:21:13.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}美国的工程师们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}American engineers
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.42,0:21:15.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}向月球发送了一束无线电波\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}bounced a beam of radio waves off the Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.02,0:21:18.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并成功地检测到了它的回波\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and were able to detect its echo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.00,0:21:28.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们把这项实验称为黛安娜计划\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They called this experiment Project Diana.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.04,0:21:29.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是由人类发出的首次\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was the first interstellar message
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.70,0:21:31.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}星际信息传递\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ever sent by our species...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.21,0:21:36.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是一段听起来很怪异的钟声\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an eerie, tolling bell.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.88,0:21:41.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只要发挥一下无限的想象力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If one allows the imagination free reign,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.65,0:21:44.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}无限的可能性会涌现出来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}many future possibilities appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.89,0:21:49.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}载人太空飞船上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Spaceships, carrying passengers
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.69,0:21:51.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当它以每小时数千英里的速度行驶时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it thousands of miles per hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.63,0:21:53.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们能有效地控制它\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can be controlled
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.53,0:21:55.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并且建立起通讯连接\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and communication established
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.70,0:21:57.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与飞船上的乘客交谈\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with their passengers,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.40,0:22:00.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为现在我们已经知道了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for we now know that the Earth's atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.07,0:22:01.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球的大气是可以被穿透的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can be penetrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.58,0:22:09.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}物体以光速行进时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Traveling at the speed of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.84,0:22:11.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只需要1秒钟\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it takes just over one second
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.18,0:22:13.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就能让无线电波抵达月面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for a radio wave to reach the lunar surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.92,0:22:18.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但扩散开来的波阵面比月球更大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the expanding wavefront is much bigger than the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.85,0:22:21.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大部分的电波会从月球旁边经过\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of the wave passes right by it,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.39,0:22:23.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只有中央部位的电波会反弹回来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the central part gets bounced back.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.66,0:22:28.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}经过2.5秒的来回时间后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}After a round-trip travel time of two and a half seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.66,0:22:30.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}电波回到了地球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it hits our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.40,0:22:33.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}黛安娜计划传输了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Project Diana transmitted
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.43,0:22:35.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一连串的强烈无线电波\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a series of powerful radio waves--
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.24,0:22:36.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每隔4秒发送1次\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one every four seconds--
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.67,0:22:38.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}好比是我们在"Ping"月亮\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to "ping" the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.67,0:22:38.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}ping:用来测试数据包能否通过IP协议到达特定主机
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.08,0:22:44.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那些没有抵达月亮的电波仍会继续旅行\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The parts that missed the Moon are traveling still.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.45,0:22:49.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这仅仅是个开端\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was just the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.38,0:22:50.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}二战后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}After World War II,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.95,0:22:54.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}美国各地的电视台遍地开花\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}television stations cropped up all over the United States,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.06,0:22:55.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}世界各地也同样如此\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and other parts of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.09,0:22:58.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}黛安娜计划发送的信息\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Project Diana message
